==English==
===Etymology===
from the [[Ojibwe]] word ''maashkinoozhe'', meaning "ugly pike," by way of [[French language|French]] ''masque allongé'' (modified from the Ojibwe word by [[folk etymology]]), "long mask."
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''muskellunge'''
# a large [[freshwater]] [[pike]], ''[[Esox masquinongy]]'', native to parts of the [[United States]] and [[Canada]]

===Synonyms===
*[[muskie]]
*[[maskinonge]]

